   Software / Hardware / Everywhere
   May 21–22, 2014 • San Francisco, CA
     __________________________________________________________________

   Internet of Things Chat on Twitter

#IoTChat with @OReillySolid

   When: Thursday, May 15th | 1-2 PM PST (4-5 PM EST)
   Where: #IoTChat on Twitter or #IoTChat on Twubs
   To add to your calendar: RSVP to the event on G+
   Topic: #manufacturing

   Join #IoTChat Tweet Chat with Solid's Jim Stogdill, Jon Bruner and
   special guest Cory Kidd of MyAutom for fun bantering and prize
   giveaways.

   New manufacturing-as-a-service frameworks make factory work fast and
   capital-light. It’s becoming easier to serve niches with specialized
   hardware that’s designed for a single purpose. This chat takes on the
   topic of the manufacturing renaissance coming upon us and features
   heavy hitters in the industry including Brady Forrest of PCH's Hardware
   Incubator Highway 1 and Amanda Parkes, Chief of Technology & Research
   at ManufactureNY.

   Grab your coffee and join #IoTChat for some fun bantering and
   entertainment. Connect with experts & heavy hitters in the IoT industry
   for an hour of intense conversation, thought-provoking questions and
   polls, and plenty of networking.

